Package: opal
Title: The open population assessment library
Version: 0.0.1
Authors@R: c(
    person("Darcy", "Webber", , "darcy@quantifish.co.nz", role = "aut"),
    person("Philipp", "Neubauer", , "philipp@dragonfly.co.nz", role = "aut"),
    person("Nicholas", "Ducharme-Barth", , "nicholas.ducharme-barth@noaa.gov", role = c("aut", "cre"))
  )
Description: A fast, flexible, and modern R package for fisheries stock assessment. 
    Built on RTMB, opal provides a powerful framework for conducting quantitative 
    population dynamics modeling and stock assessment analyses. Designed for fisheries 
    scientists and stock assessment analysts who need transparent, reproducible, and 
    collaborative tools for population assessment.
